        <h1 id="Metadata">SPASE Base Model</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="body">
<p>The SPASE metadata model can be expressed in many forms. One of those forms is as an XML Schema.
	An XML Schema is a machine readable form (see <a taget="_blank" href="http://www.spase-group.org/data/schema/">schema<span class="tutor">View the SPASE XML Schema</span></a>). Here you can find
	human readable documentation which includes standard model diagrams.
</p>
<p>
	Each version of the metadata model is fully documented. The available versions are available at: <a target="_blank" href="http://www.spase-group.org/data/model/">http://www.spase-group.org/data/model/<span class="tutor">View documentation on the SPASE Information Model.</span></a>
</p>
